This happens with a monitoring system that creates an action, executes it, and then deletes it, which operates every 5 minutes. I expect the container to be reused "indefinitely", since the 10 minute "unused" limit is not reached, and there is not additional traffic in the system (to cause the container to get destroyed so other actions can run). 

It does NOT happen (no Connection reset errors) if the action is created each time with a unique name. 
  
So far I am not able to reproduce locally, unfortunately.

